	<transcript sound="sound1"><![CDATA[Welcome to module 7.<br /><br />In this module we'll learn about food premises and equipment.<br/><br/>You'll need approximately 15 minutes to complete this module. We will understand:<li>Why it is necessary to design, construct and maintain premises and equipment;</li><li>The role of the food handler in preventing hazards from food premises and equipment; and</li><li>What care should be taken when storing and disposing of waste.</li><br />Food premises and equipment should be designed and constructed to ensure that food is not exposed to risk of contamination.<br /><br />Food handlers must be aware of the hazards associated with food premises and equipment.<br/><br/>Click the icon to learn what the law says about food premises and equipment.<br/><br/> When you have finished, click the 'Next' button to continue.]]></transcript>

